Hone Tuwhare (21 October 1922 – 16 January 2008) was a noted New Zealand poet of Māori ancestry.
Hone Tuwhare was awarded the Robert Burns Fellowship from the University of Otago in 1969 and again in 1974.
At the time of his death Hone Tuwhare was described as "New Zealand's most distinguished Maori writer"*.
